===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# [[fragmented|Fragmented]], in separate pieces.
## {{label|en|of a|bone or body part}} [[fractured|Fractured]]; having the bone in pieces.
##: ''My arm is '''broken'''!''
##: ''the ground was littered with '''broken''' bones''
## {{label|en|of skin}} Split or [[ruptured]].
##: ''A dog bit my leg and now the skin is '''broken'''.''
## {{label|en|of a|line}} Dashed, made up of short lines with small gaps between each one and the next.
## {{label|en|of sleep}} Interrupted; not continuous.
##* {{rfdate}}, [[w:Jack London|Jack London]], ''White Fang'':
##*: Then the circle would lie down again, and here and there a wolf would resume its '''broken''' nap.
## {{label|en|meteorology|of the sky}} Five-[[eighth]]s to seven-eighths [[obscure|obscured]] by clouds; incompletely covered by clouds.
##: ''Tomorrow: '''broken''' skies.''
# {{label|en|of a|promise, etc}} [[breeched|Breeched]]; [[violated]]; not kept.
#: '''''broken''' promises of neutrality'', '''''broken''' vows'', ''the '''broken''' covenant''
# Non-functional; not functioning properly.
#: ''I think my doorbell '''broken'''.''
## {{label|en|of an|electronic connection}} [[disconnected|Disconnected]], no longer open or carrying traffic.
## {{label|en|software|informal}} [[badly|Badly]] [[designed]] or [[implemented]].
##: ''This is the most '''broken''' application I've seen in a long time.''
## {{label|en|pejorative|of language}} [[grammatical|Grammatically]] non-standard, especially as a result of being a [[non-native speaker]].
## {{label|en|colloquial|US|of a|situation}} Not having gone in the way intended; [[saddening]].
##: ''Oh man! That is just '''broken'''!''
# {{label|en|of a|person}} Completely [[defeated]] and [[dispirited]]; [[shattered]]; [[destroyed]].
#: ''The bankruptcy and divorce, together with the death of his son, left him completely '''broken'''.''
# Having no money; [[bankrupt]], [[broke]].
#: {{rfquote-sense}}
# {{label|en|of land}} [[uneven|Uneven]].
#* '''2005''', Will Cook, ''Until Darkness Disappears'', page 54:
#*: All that day they rode into '''broken''' land. The prairie with its grass and rolling hills was behind them, and they entered a sparse, dry, rocky country, full of draws and short cañons and ominous buttresses.
# {{label|en|sports|and|gaming|of a tactic or option}} [[overpowered|Overpowered]]; overly powerful; too powerful.

